# {{projectName}}

A Tenkit Single App Runtime Tenants project for Expo SDK 57.

This app has exactly one native App Variant and can open multiple Runtime Tenants inside that app at runtime. The App Variant owns the Slug, app name, URL scheme, bundle identifier, Android package, theme accent, EAS Project ID, icon set, splash assets, and web favicon. Runtime Tenant records live in generated source data.

## Highlights

- Built with Expo Router, TypeScript, and Expo SDK 57.
- Uses one App Variant for native app identity at config and build time.
- Bundles Runtime Tenant records under `src/constants/runtime-tenants.ts`.
- Exposes Runtime Tenant Access bootstrap data through Expo `extra` without dumping full Runtime Tenant records there.
- Includes per-App Variant assets under `assets/<app-variant-slug>/`.
- Ships with a local Tenkit CLI for build preparation: `build`, `reset`, and `doctor`.
- Includes `expo-dev-client` for native development builds and `expo-system-ui` for native UI style handling.
{{#if isUnistylesStyling}}
- Uses Unistyles for generated UI styling. Customize themes and tokens in `unistyles.ts`.
{{/if}}

## Get Started

1. Install dependencies.

   ```bash
   {{packageManagerInstallCommand}}
   ```

2. Review the generated App Variant and Runtime Tenants.

   ```text
